56
00:04:11,565 --> 00:04:13,734
So 1 out of 4 are rejects.

57
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:21,033
So you're really docking
10% off our pay?

58
00:04:21,491 --> 00:04:24,828
Considering the rejects,
that's a low penalty, isn't it?

59
00:04:25,996 --> 00:04:28,957
Our pay is so low already!
How can you do this?

60
00:04:31,168 --> 00:04:32,252
Look here.

61
00:04:32,711 --> 00:04:35,130
This is not some minor issue.

62
00:04:35,297 --> 00:04:40,052
You know what one shitty box
can do to our brand image?

63
00:04:40,093 --> 00:04:43,889
Brand? You can't even
afford a box folder!

64
00:04:44,014 --> 00:04:45,182
What did you say?

65
00:04:46,391 --> 00:04:47,267
Boss.

66
00:04:48,435 --> 00:04:49,895
This is all because
of that guy, right?

67
00:04:49,937 --> 00:04:50,854
What guy?

68
00:04:50,938 --> 00:04:54,691
Your part-time worker.
He's gone AWOL, right?

69
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:58,070
Just when the Love of God Church
made a huge group order?

70
00:04:58,111 --> 00:05:00,906
How do you know all that?

71
00:05:01,406 --> 00:05:02,658
Who told you?

72
00:05:03,033 --> 00:05:04,785
My sister knows the guy.

73
00:05:05,118 --> 00:05:09,373
He's always been a bit strange.
Got a bad reputation.

74
00:05:09,748 --> 00:05:11,500
Speaking of which, Boss.

75
00:05:12,334 --> 00:05:14,503
We'll accept a 10% penalty.

76
00:05:14,544 --> 00:05:15,420
In return...

77
00:05:15,629 --> 00:05:16,588
In return?

78
00:05:17,130 --> 00:05:19,591
Any thought of hiring
a new part-time worker?

79
00:05:19,716 --> 00:05:23,095
Sis, we need someone!

80
00:05:23,637 --> 00:05:26,723
Ditch the guy you've got now.
Just fire him.

81
00:05:27,474 --> 00:05:30,602
Tomorrow I'll come for
a formal interview. What time?

82
00:05:30,769 --> 00:05:32,229
Wait, hold on a sec.

83
00:05:33,230 --> 00:05:35,107
Let me think about it.

84
00:05:35,774 --> 00:05:38,944
Then for now,
just pay for the boxes.

85
00:05:45,575 --> 00:05:48,954
So we're all gathered here today,

86
00:05:49,579 --> 00:05:52,916
to celebrate the
reconnection of our phones,

87
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,712
and this bounteous wi-fi!

88
00:05:56,962 --> 00:06:00,132
Look at that bastard.
It's not even dark yet.

89
00:06:00,966 --> 00:06:04,636
Why didn't you put up a
'No Urinating' sign?

90
00:06:04,803 --> 00:06:05,554
I told you!

91
00:06:05,595 --> 00:06:09,641
No, signs like that just make
them piss even more.

92
00:06:10,475 --> 00:06:12,352
At least shout at him!

93
00:06:12,394 --> 00:06:13,645
Don't shout.

94
00:06:14,104 --> 00:06:15,939
"Please don't piss!"

95
00:06:17,816 --> 00:06:20,569
Hey, is that Min?

96
00:06:21,319 --> 00:06:23,488
Hey mister,
that's not a toilet.

97
00:06:23,613 --> 00:06:24,990
Way to go, Min.

98
00:06:25,032 --> 00:06:27,159
Hey, punk!

99
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:30,078
Who are you staring at,
asshole?

100
00:06:30,537 --> 00:06:33,749
Come here!
You little shit.

101
00:06:35,709 --> 00:06:37,794
Get a fucking grip!

102
00:06:39,004 --> 00:06:41,298
That's an impressive friend.

103
00:06:41,339 --> 00:06:44,176
College students have
a real vigor to them.

104
00:06:44,509 --> 00:06:45,385
Not like my brother.

105
00:06:45,552 --> 00:06:48,805
But is he coming here?
Did you invite him?

106
00:06:49,056 --> 00:06:49,765
No.

107
00:06:50,223 --> 00:06:51,183
Hello!

108
00:06:51,349 --> 00:06:52,684
Oh hi, Min!

109
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,186
Min!

110
00:06:54,227 --> 00:06:55,103
Are you well, sir?

111
00:06:55,145 --> 00:06:57,689
- Sure.
- What are you doing here?

112
00:06:57,731 --> 00:06:59,191
I texted you.
Didn't you see it?

113
00:06:59,941 --> 00:07:01,026
Sorry, were you eating?

114
00:07:01,234 --> 00:07:02,486
No, we weren't eating.

115
00:07:02,527 --> 00:07:04,696
- How are you, Ki-jung?
- Fine, you too?

116
00:07:04,863 --> 00:07:07,532
We could've met outside,
why come here?

117
00:07:07,741 --> 00:07:08,533
Because of this.

118
00:07:08,575 --> 00:07:11,328
It's for you,
but it's so heavy.

119
00:07:11,536 --> 00:07:13,497
Really?
Put it down here.

120
00:07:15,832 --> 00:07:17,334
Wow, what is that?

121
00:07:17,584 --> 00:07:19,127
When I said I was meeting Ki-woo,

122
00:07:19,252 --> 00:07:22,130
my grandfather insisted
I bring this to you.

123
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:28,845
Is this a landscape type?

124
00:07:30,347 --> 00:07:32,224
Or you can see it as
an abstract type.

125
00:07:32,265 --> 00:07:33,850
Wow, you know these!

126
00:07:34,101 --> 00:07:38,063
My grandpa has collected
scholar's rocks since his cadet days.

127
00:07:38,188 --> 00:07:41,650
Now the annex, the study,
every room in the house

128
00:07:41,858 --> 00:07:43,819
is filled with these things.

129
00:07:43,902 --> 00:07:47,864
But this stone here is said to
bring material wealth to families...

130
00:07:47,906 --> 00:07:48,865
Min!

131
00:07:49,407 --> 00:07:52,327
This is so metaphorical.

132
00:07:52,619 --> 00:07:55,664
For sure.
It's a very opportune gift.

133
00:07:55,997 --> 00:07:56,748
Of course.

134
00:07:56,790 --> 00:08:00,544
Please relay our deepest thanks
to your grandpa.

135
00:08:01,294 --> 00:08:02,838
Food would be better.

136
00:08:12,931 --> 00:08:15,892
What was that called?
A landscape stone?

137
00:08:16,226 --> 00:08:17,561
You collect those rocks too?

138
00:08:17,644 --> 00:08:22,065
Hey, thanks to that rock I saw
your parents, they look healthy.

139
00:08:23,650 --> 00:08:27,571
They're plenty healthy,
just out of work.

140
00:08:30,031 --> 00:08:32,617
Is Ki-jung taking lessons
these days?

141
00:08:33,451 --> 00:08:36,204
She can't afford lessons.

142
00:08:45,172 --> 00:08:46,423
Cute, huh?

143
00:08:47,465 --> 00:08:49,926
She's the one you're tutoring?

144
00:08:50,051 --> 00:08:52,220
Park Da-hye.
High school sophomore.

145
00:08:52,637 --> 00:08:55,640
You take over as her English tutor.

146
00:08:56,349 --> 00:08:57,225
What do you mean?

147
00:08:57,350 --> 00:08:59,519
Tutor a rich kid.
It pays well.

148
00:09:00,770 --> 00:09:01,938
She's a nice girl.

149
00:09:02,147 --> 00:09:05,150
Look after her while
I'm studying abroad.

150
00:09:05,942 --> 00:09:09,237
What about your
university friends?

151
00:09:09,487 --> 00:09:12,741
Why ask a loser like me?

152
00:09:13,283 --> 00:09:14,659
Why do you think?

153
00:09:15,452 --> 00:09:17,621
Just the thought makes me sick.

154
00:09:17,704 --> 00:09:21,833
Those disgusting frat boys
slavering over Da-hye?

155
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,960
It's revolting.

156
00:09:29,799 --> 00:09:30,967
You like her?

157
00:09:36,014 --> 00:09:38,183
Hey, I'm serious.

158
00:09:39,476 --> 00:09:43,647
When she enters university,
I'll officially ask her out.

159
00:09:44,105 --> 00:09:45,857
So you take care of her
until then.

160
00:09:45,982 --> 00:09:50,153
If it's you,
I can leave in peace.

161
00:09:51,696 --> 00:09:54,366
Thanks for your trust,

162
00:09:54,824 --> 00:09:58,286
but do I have to pretend
to be a college student?

163
00:09:59,996 --> 00:10:02,791
Ki-woo, think about it.

164
00:10:03,541 --> 00:10:07,003
For years including
your military service,

165
00:10:07,212 --> 00:10:09,214
you took the university
entrance exam 4 times.

166
00:10:09,631 --> 00:10:12,300
Grammar, vocabulary,
composition, conversation...

167
00:10:13,009 --> 00:10:14,678
When it comes to English,

168
00:10:14,761 --> 00:10:18,807
you can teach 10 times better than
those drunken college pricks.

169
00:10:20,558 --> 00:10:22,894
- I guess so.
- Sure!

170
00:10:23,436 --> 00:10:26,982
But will they hire me?
I'm not a college student.

171
00:10:27,232 --> 00:10:28,692
Just fake it.

172
00:10:28,858 --> 00:10:32,612
Don't worry, you'll have
my recommendation, plus...

173
00:10:33,530 --> 00:10:36,324
How should I describe the mother...?

174
00:10:38,576 --> 00:10:39,995
She's a bit simple.

175
00:10:40,245 --> 00:10:41,329
<i>Young and simple.</i>

176
00:10:41,454 --> 00:10:42,247
Simple?

177
00:10:43,081 --> 00:10:44,416
What do you mean?

178
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:48,545
Anyway, it's all good.
I had fun there.

179
00:10:49,296 --> 00:10:50,422
So you agree?

180
00:10:50,547 --> 00:10:52,007
I guess so.

181
00:10:53,383 --> 00:10:57,137
Hey, you said your sister
is artistic?

182
00:10:57,387 --> 00:10:58,430
Good at Photoshop?

183
00:11:01,683 --> 00:11:05,770
God, with skills like this,
why can't you get into art school?

184
00:11:05,895 --> 00:11:07,147
Shut up.

185
00:11:09,691 --> 00:11:11,860
Hey, no smoking in here.

186
00:11:11,901 --> 00:11:13,361
Yeah, yeah.
Gimme that.

187
00:11:13,403 --> 00:11:14,279
Yeah.

188
00:11:18,908 --> 00:11:21,578
Now the cherry on top...

189
00:11:23,121 --> 00:11:27,667
Wow, does Oxford have a major
in document forgery?

190
00:11:27,917 --> 00:11:31,171
Ki-jung would be top of her class.

191
00:11:31,421 --> 00:11:34,090
She's amazing, huh?

192
00:11:34,215 --> 00:11:39,387
Our boy's going for a job interview.
Wish him luck.

193
00:11:40,138 --> 00:11:40,889
Son.

194
00:11:42,307 --> 00:11:44,893
I'm proud of you.

195
00:11:45,352 --> 00:11:46,269
Dad.

196
00:11:47,354 --> 00:11:50,315
I don't think of this
as forgery or crime.

197
00:11:50,732 --> 00:11:52,692
I'll go to this university
next year.

198
00:11:52,817 --> 00:11:56,196
So you've got a plan!

199
00:11:56,363 --> 00:12:00,200
I just printed out
the document a bit early.

200
00:12:35,693 --> 00:12:36,653
<i>Who is it?</i>

201
00:12:37,404 --> 00:12:39,364
Madame?
Good afternoon.

202
00:12:39,489 --> 00:12:41,324
I'm here on
Min's recommendation...

203
00:12:41,366 --> 00:12:43,159
<i>Oh right, come in.</i>

204
00:12:44,411 --> 00:12:45,161
Thank you.

205
00:13:17,318 --> 00:13:18,486
Hello!

206
00:13:19,529 --> 00:13:20,697
Hello, Madame.

207
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:24,159
I just work here.
Come this way.

208
00:13:24,951 --> 00:13:26,578
The yard is so nice.

209
00:13:26,744 --> 00:13:27,996
The inside's nice too.

210
00:13:28,705 --> 00:13:31,916
You know the architect Namgoong?
He's famous.

211
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:34,669
He used to live in this house.

212
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:39,007
He designed it himself.

213
00:13:42,135 --> 00:13:47,015
As you can see,
now it's a playpen.

214
00:13:47,557 --> 00:13:48,516
This way.

215
00:13:51,144 --> 00:13:53,521
Sit yourself down here.
I'll bring the madame.

216
00:13:53,646 --> 00:13:54,439
Yes.

217
00:14:06,951 --> 00:14:08,119
<i>Madame.</i>

218
00:14:09,162 --> 00:14:10,330
<i>Madame?</i>

219
00:14:13,082 --> 00:14:14,250
Madame?

220
00:14:16,169 --> 00:14:17,337
Madame?

221
00:14:21,174 --> 00:14:23,343
He's here.
The tutoring candidate.

222
00:14:27,096 --> 00:14:29,057
I don't care about documents.

223
00:14:29,807 --> 00:14:32,352
Min recommended you,
after all.

224
00:14:33,186 --> 00:14:38,942
As you know, Min is such
a <i>brilliant</i> human being.

225
00:14:39,817 --> 00:14:41,986
Da-hye and I were
quite happy with him.

226
00:14:42,111 --> 00:14:45,156
Regardless of her grades.
Know what I mean?

227
00:14:45,490 --> 00:14:46,241
Yes.

228
00:14:46,908 --> 00:14:48,743
He was marvelous.

229
00:14:48,826 --> 00:14:55,750
So to be honest, we wanted to stick
with him through high school.

230
00:14:56,417 --> 00:14:59,587
But all of a sudden
he's going abroad.

231
00:15:02,131 --> 00:15:07,387
Anyway, excuse me,
but if I can speak directly,

232
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:12,517
if you're not up to
Min's level, then,

233
00:15:12,642 --> 00:15:14,686
I'm not sure what the point is.

234
00:15:16,854 --> 00:15:20,608
So anyway,
what I want to say is,

235
00:15:20,942 --> 00:15:26,406
for your first lesson today,
do you mind if I sit in?

236
00:15:26,656 --> 00:15:30,326
I want to see it <i>full time,</i>
how you run your lesson.

237
00:15:32,453 --> 00:15:34,414
<i>Is it okay with you?</i>

238
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,360
You sure about #24?

239
00:16:12,410 --> 00:16:17,248
Da-hye, you solved those later
problems then went back to #24.

240
00:16:17,498 --> 00:16:18,833
Right?

241
00:16:20,501 --> 00:16:21,669
Yes.

242
00:16:29,636 --> 00:16:34,766
If that were the first question
on a real exam, you'd be screwed.

243
00:16:35,516 --> 00:16:38,978
Look at this.
Your pulse is racing.

244
00:16:41,648 --> 00:16:44,901
The heart doesn't lie.

245
00:16:45,943 --> 00:16:49,280
An exam is like
slashing through a jungle.

246
00:16:49,447 --> 00:16:51,991
Lose that momentum
and you're finished.

247
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:54,702
The answer to #24?
I don't care.

248
00:16:54,952 --> 00:16:59,999
Slashing through the exam,
dominating it!

249
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,418
That's all I care about.

250
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:07,131
What you need is vigor.

251
00:17:08,549 --> 00:17:09,634
Vigor.

252
00:17:11,052 --> 00:17:12,136
Understand?

253
00:17:23,481 --> 00:17:26,234
So I'll pay you
this time each month.

254
00:17:26,359 --> 00:17:29,237
3 classes a week,
2 hours each, okay?

255
00:17:30,363 --> 00:17:31,406
As for the fee,

256
00:17:31,489 --> 00:17:35,159
I was going to pay Min's rate,
then I added a bit for inflation.

257
00:17:35,368 --> 00:17:36,536
Thank you.

258
00:17:38,454 --> 00:17:40,248
How about a
proper introduction?

259
00:17:40,498 --> 00:17:43,126
Da-hye's tutor,
we'll call him Kevin.

260
00:17:44,085 --> 00:17:45,461
Mr. Kevin!

261
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:49,424
If you feel like snacking during
your lesson, just call me.

262
00:17:49,799 --> 00:17:51,759
If you need anything, ask her.

263
00:17:52,009 --> 00:17:54,262
She knows this house
better than I...

264
00:17:54,595 --> 00:17:57,849
