00:34:26,086 --> 00:34:27,629
Not that!

526
00:34:28,505 --> 00:34:34,261
Still, for a busy man like me to ask,
"Why are you fucking in my car?"

527
00:34:34,386 --> 00:34:35,470
Exactly.

528
00:34:35,595 --> 00:34:37,347
So instead...

529
00:34:37,514 --> 00:34:42,352
Can you just invent some
bland excuse to let him go?

530
00:34:42,686 --> 00:34:43,979
Okay sure.

531
00:34:44,104 --> 00:34:47,190
No need to mention
panties or car sex.

532
00:34:47,607 --> 00:34:49,651
We don't need to stoop
to that level, do we?

533
00:34:49,693 --> 00:34:51,361
Surely not!

534
00:34:51,987 --> 00:34:55,157
But what if he goes online
and accuses us...

535
00:34:55,198 --> 00:34:56,867
Just give him a good severance.

536
00:34:57,701 --> 00:35:00,871
How was Da-song today?

537
00:35:01,121 --> 00:35:02,873
He was fine.

538
00:35:03,623 --> 00:35:05,792
- So class is finished?
- Yes.

539
00:35:05,917 --> 00:35:08,587
Jessica, the last time you came,

540
00:35:08,628 --> 00:35:11,006
our driver gave you a ride, right?

541
00:35:11,131 --> 00:35:12,090
That's right.

542
00:35:12,132 --> 00:35:14,217
This may be an odd question,

543
00:35:14,551 --> 00:35:16,094
but nothing happened then?

544
00:35:16,553 --> 00:35:18,013
No, he was very nice.

545
00:35:18,054 --> 00:35:19,973
I told him to go
to Hyehwa Station,

546
00:35:20,015 --> 00:35:23,226
but he insisted on
driving me home.

547
00:35:23,351 --> 00:35:26,480
That jerk!
He took you home late at night?

548
00:35:26,646 --> 00:35:27,981
Revealing where you live?

549
00:35:29,065 --> 00:35:31,526
No, I got off at Hyehwa.

550
00:35:31,735 --> 00:35:33,737
Oh, good girl. Very good.

551
00:35:34,154 --> 00:35:35,405
<i>Jessica nice...</i>

552
00:35:35,781 --> 00:35:37,908
Did something happen with him?

553
00:35:38,283 --> 00:35:43,330
He won't be working for us any more.
A slightly shameful incident.

554
00:35:43,580 --> 00:35:45,499
What incident?

555
00:35:45,665 --> 00:35:48,251
Oh, you don't need to know.

556
00:35:49,878 --> 00:35:53,757
But I'm surprised.
He was so gentlemanly and cool.

557
00:35:53,882 --> 00:35:57,135
Jessica, you're too
young and innocent!

558
00:35:57,302 --> 00:35:59,054
You have a lot to learn about people.

559
00:36:00,096 --> 00:36:04,935
But we were excited to have
such a young, hip driver, too.

560
00:36:05,101 --> 00:36:08,271
But isn't an older driver better?

561
00:36:08,396 --> 00:36:12,150
That's true. They drive better,
have better manners.

562
00:36:12,484 --> 00:36:15,070
My father's brother had
a driver just like that.

563
00:36:15,195 --> 00:36:19,658
Mr. Kim.
He was so congenial and nice,

564
00:36:19,783 --> 00:36:22,369
I used to call him Uncle
when I was young.

565
00:36:22,410 --> 00:36:24,371
You know a man like that?

566
00:36:24,496 --> 00:36:27,165
Yes, he was so mild-mannered.

567
00:36:28,083 --> 00:36:32,462
Oh, but my relatives
relocated to Chicago.

568
00:36:33,922 --> 00:36:35,882
I wonder if
Mr. Kim's free now?

569
00:36:36,216 --> 00:36:40,178
I'm really interested!
Could I meet him?

570
00:36:40,303 --> 00:36:41,388
Really?

571
00:36:41,429 --> 00:36:43,473
I don't trust anyone now.

572
00:36:44,307 --> 00:36:47,185
I only trust someone recommended
by a person I know well.

573
00:36:47,352 --> 00:36:51,690
But if you've known him so long,
I'd feel much more at ease.

574
00:36:54,651 --> 00:36:56,319
Do you really want to meet him?

575
00:36:57,153 --> 00:36:58,405
<i>I'm deadly serious.</i>

576
00:36:59,114 --> 00:37:02,492
This chain of
recommendations is best.

577
00:37:03,034 --> 00:37:04,202
How should I describe it?

578
00:37:04,744 --> 00:37:05,829
A belt of trust?

579
00:37:06,454 --> 00:37:07,706
- This one's different.
- Here.

580
00:37:07,747 --> 00:37:08,415
Oh, right.

581
00:37:08,456 --> 00:37:09,708
And this one.

582
00:37:10,166 --> 00:37:11,793
Looks like a touch screen now.

583
00:37:11,835 --> 00:37:14,796
It's not touch,
it says you have to turn it.

584
00:37:14,838 --> 00:37:16,506
Wow, this thing?

585
00:37:17,257 --> 00:37:18,091
Sir?

586
00:37:18,383 --> 00:37:20,427
Taking our time, are we?

587
00:37:23,638 --> 00:37:24,806
This is a nice car.

588
00:37:27,392 --> 00:37:29,352
This is it! Come over here.

589
00:37:33,064 --> 00:37:34,232
He's in a meeting now.

590
00:37:39,487 --> 00:37:41,323
Have a seat and wait here.

591
00:37:50,290 --> 00:37:53,376
Hello, nice to meet...

592
00:37:56,880 --> 00:37:58,340
But is it compatible
with a phone?

593
00:37:58,423 --> 00:38:04,763
Oh, not with a phone.
You need more computing power.

594
00:38:06,222 --> 00:38:10,560
This isn't any sort of test,
so don't be nervous.

595
00:38:11,436 --> 00:38:14,356
I was worn out at the office,
so I came out for a bit.

596
00:38:15,190 --> 00:38:16,191
I understand.

597
00:38:16,441 --> 00:38:20,695
Constant chatter, all that bother.
At least the car is peaceful.

598
00:38:23,448 --> 00:38:24,407
Thank you.

599
00:38:25,533 --> 00:38:26,910
You seem to know
the roads well?

600
00:38:27,118 --> 00:38:30,163
Anything below the 38th parallel.

601
00:38:30,538 --> 00:38:33,416
After 30 years behind the wheel,
the car almost drives itself.

602
00:38:34,042 --> 00:38:36,586
I respect those who work
in one field for a long time.

603
00:38:37,212 --> 00:38:39,923
Well, to be honest,
this is a simple vocation.

604
00:38:39,965 --> 00:38:42,926
But... the head of a household,

605
00:38:43,551 --> 00:38:45,011
the leader of a company?

606
00:38:45,470 --> 00:38:50,225
Or else just a lonely man setting off
on the road each morning...

607
00:38:51,059 --> 00:38:52,894
It's companionship of a sort,

608
00:38:53,353 --> 00:38:56,106
so that's how
I've approached each day.

609
00:38:56,356 --> 00:38:58,400
The years sure pass quickly.

610
00:39:01,987 --> 00:39:04,239
Sure enough,
your cornering is excellent.

611
00:39:05,281 --> 00:39:11,329
Well, it may look simple,
but it's one of the fundamentals.

612
00:39:11,788 --> 00:39:16,209
<i>She may look like a sheep,
but inside, she's a fox.</i>

613
00:39:16,668 --> 00:39:19,421
<i>Sometimes she acts like
she owns the house.</i>

614
00:39:20,296 --> 00:39:21,047
<i>Right.</i>

615
00:39:21,381 --> 00:39:25,760
<i>Of all the people in that house,
she's lived there the longest.</i>

616
00:39:25,969 --> 00:39:29,556
<i>She was housekeeper
to the architect Namgoong,</i>

617
00:39:29,681 --> 00:39:34,060
<i>but then she went on
to work for this family.</i>

618
00:39:34,602 --> 00:39:36,271
<i>When the architect moved out,</i>

619
00:39:36,396 --> 00:39:39,274
<i>he introduced this woman
to Park's family,</i>

620
00:39:39,399 --> 00:39:42,360
<i>telling them, "This is a great
housekeeper, you should hire her."</i>

621
00:39:42,610 --> 00:39:45,989
<i>So she survived
a change of ownership.</i>

622
00:39:46,281 --> 00:39:48,992
She won't give up a good job easily.

623
00:39:49,534 --> 00:39:52,662
To extract a woman like that,
we need to prepare well.

624
00:39:54,330 --> 00:39:56,666
Right, we need a plan.

625
00:39:58,043 --> 00:40:01,296
I want to eat peaches.
I like peaches best.

626
00:40:01,838 --> 00:40:03,089
Why not ask for some?

627
00:40:03,339 --> 00:40:06,801
No peaches at our house.
It's forbidden fruit.

628
00:40:14,809 --> 00:40:17,687
<i>So according to what
Da-hye told me,</i>

629
00:40:17,729 --> 00:40:22,025
<i>she's got a massively serious
allergy to peaches.</i>

630
00:40:22,442 --> 00:40:25,528
<i>You know that fuzz
on a peach's skin?</i>

631
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:29,491
<i>If she's anywhere near it,
she gets a full body rash,</i>

632
00:40:29,532 --> 00:40:33,119
<i>has trouble breathing,
asthma, a total meltdown!</i>

633
00:40:37,749 --> 00:40:41,836
No no, there weren't
any peaches anywhere.

634
00:40:43,838 --> 00:40:45,924
That's what I'm saying!

635
00:40:46,466 --> 00:40:48,843
Usually when I get
symptoms like this,

636
00:40:49,094 --> 00:40:52,222
I run to my room
and take my medicine,

637
00:40:52,597 --> 00:40:57,852
but it was so sudden,
I wasn't sure where I left it.

638
00:40:58,103 --> 00:41:02,816
Madame, this woman
behind me, is that...?

639
00:41:03,191 --> 00:41:05,068
Oh, it's our housekeeper!

640
00:41:05,193 --> 00:41:07,570
So it's true.
Oh, how sad.

641
00:41:07,987 --> 00:41:10,740
I wasn't sure if that
was really her.

642
00:41:11,074 --> 00:41:14,452
I've only seen her a couple times
in the living room.

643
00:41:15,286 --> 00:41:17,163
This was in the hospital?

644
00:41:17,413 --> 00:41:21,042
A few days ago I went for
my annual medical exam.

645
00:41:21,709 --> 00:41:25,880
I took a selfie for my wife,
and there she was behind me.

646
00:41:26,422 --> 00:41:28,591
Is she talking
on the phone there?

647
00:41:28,633 --> 00:41:31,845
Anyway. I wasn't trying to eavesdrop...

648
00:41:31,886 --> 00:41:33,471
I wasn't trying to eavesdrop,

649
00:41:33,888 --> 00:41:35,598
but her words came through clearly!

650
00:41:35,807 --> 00:41:37,392
- So I couldn't help but...!
- Cut, cut!

651
00:41:37,642 --> 00:41:40,562
Dad, your emotions are up to here.

652
00:41:40,603 --> 00:41:42,480
Bring them down to about there.

653
00:41:43,148 --> 00:41:45,900
...so I couldn't help but overhear.

654
00:41:45,942 --> 00:41:48,361
Keep it focused!

655
00:41:50,029 --> 00:41:52,574
What I'm trying to say is,
it's just that,

656
00:41:52,615 --> 00:41:56,494
your housekeeper's voice
is quite loud, you know?

657
00:41:56,953 --> 00:42:00,582
I understand, it's all right.
Just tell me, okay?

658
00:42:00,623 --> 00:42:03,501
She said she got diagnosed
with active TB,

659
00:42:03,543 --> 00:42:05,503
and she was shouting
on the phone,

660
00:42:05,670 --> 00:42:08,715
so upset she could
barely control herself!

661
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:11,217
Tuberculosis? Come on...

662
00:42:11,259 --> 00:42:16,306
It's true, she phoned someone
saying she had active TB.

663
00:42:16,973 --> 00:42:19,017
Do people still get TB?

664
00:42:19,184 --> 00:42:21,436
Do people still get TB?

665
00:42:21,978 --> 00:42:22,645
Dad...

666
00:42:23,062 --> 00:42:28,234
Back in the day, people used
to buy Christmas Seals, right?

667
00:42:28,359 --> 00:42:29,652
Feels like a bygone era.

668
00:42:29,777 --> 00:42:31,321
But I saw it on the internet.

669
00:42:31,571 --> 00:42:35,158
Korea has the #1 rate of TB
of all the OECD countries.

670
00:42:35,491 --> 00:42:38,828
But she's still working,
as if nothing's wrong.

671
00:42:39,078 --> 00:42:41,039
With a kid like Da-song
in the house.

672
00:42:41,164 --> 00:42:44,167
So you've got a young kid
like Da-song in the house,

673
00:42:44,500 --> 00:42:47,629
and a TB patient is doing dishes,
cooking, spraying spittle...

674
00:42:47,879 --> 00:42:49,172
Stop it, please!

675
00:42:53,801 --> 00:42:55,470
<i>Dad: Arriving in 3 mins</i>

676
00:43:42,350 --> 00:43:46,020
If you get the chance,
this'll be icing on the cake.

677
00:44:16,551 --> 00:44:18,261
<i>- Madame -</i>

678
00:44:18,303 --> 00:44:20,138
<i>2nd floor sauna room</i>

679
00:44:20,179 --> 00:44:21,347
<i>Don't let her see you</i>

680
00:44:31,774 --> 00:44:33,026
- Have a seat.
- Yes.

681
00:44:35,486 --> 00:44:36,279
Mr. Kim.

682
00:44:36,612 --> 00:44:40,366
Please don't tell any of this
to my husband, okay?

683
00:44:40,783 --> 00:44:41,659
Understood.

684
00:44:41,909 --> 00:44:46,247
If he hears I brought a
TB patient to our home,

685
00:44:46,706 --> 00:44:49,375
I'll be hanged
and quartered!

686
00:44:49,584 --> 00:44:51,169
Don't worry, Madame.

687
00:44:51,586 --> 00:44:54,881
And if I may presume
to say one thing.

688
00:44:55,298 --> 00:44:58,259
I have no feelings
against that woman.

689
00:44:58,926 --> 00:45:06,184
I felt I had to speak up for the
sake of public health and hygiene.

690
00:45:06,601 --> 00:45:10,104
But this could be seen
as snitching or...

691
00:45:10,229 --> 00:45:11,606
Don't you worry.

692
00:45:11,731 --> 00:45:14,275
I won't mention the TB.

693
00:45:14,359 --> 00:45:16,694
I'll just make up some excuse
to dismiss her.

694
00:45:16,944 --> 00:45:18,112
Simply and quietly.

695
00:45:20,031 --> 00:45:22,617
It's a proven method.
That's the best.

696
00:45:22,867 --> 00:45:24,410
Okay, then.

697
00:45:35,671 --> 00:45:38,633
Have you...
washed your hands?

698
00:46:24,387 --> 00:46:28,558
Mr. Kim, do you know
a good braised ribs place?

699
00:46:28,683 --> 00:46:30,268
Somewhere close by.

700
00:46:30,435 --> 00:46:31,477
Sure.

701
00:46:31,894 --> 00:46:35,273
- Then you'll be eating out?
- That's right.

702
00:46:36,232 --> 00:46:38,860
Why such a craving for
braised ribs today?

703
00:46:39,444 --> 00:46:42,280
Our old housekeeper made
delicious ribs.

704
00:46:43,322 --> 00:46:45,783
The one who quit this week?

705
00:46:45,825 --> 00:46:50,413
My wife wouldn't even
tell me why she quit.

706
00:46:53,416 --> 00:46:58,421
Sure, it's easy enough
to hire a new one.

707
00:46:59,630 --> 00:47:04,427
Still, it's a shame.
She was a great housekeeper.

708
00:47:04,552 --> 00:47:05,428
I see.

709
00:47:05,553 --> 00:47:08,014
She kept the house
in great shape,

710
00:47:08,222 --> 00:47:10,516
and she knew never to
cross the line.

711
00:47:11,434 --> 00:47:13,936
I can't stand people
who cross the line.

712
00:47:14,645 --> 00:47:17,190
Perhaps just one weak point?

713
00:47:18,149 --> 00:47:19,525
Eating too much.

714
00:47:19,734 --> 00:47:22,320
She always ate enough for two.

715
00:47:23,279 --> 00:47:27,033
But considering
all the work she did...

716
00:47:27,283 --> 00:47:32,455
Then you better find someone new.
A new housekeeper.

717
00:47:32,747 --> 00:47:34,540
We're in trouble now.

718
00:47:34,874 --> 00:47:38,961
In a week,
our house will be a trash can.

719
00:47:40,087 --> 00:47:43,049
My clothes will start to smell.

720
00:47:44,300 --> 00:47:47,136
My wife has no talent
for housework.

721
00:47:47,386 --> 00:47:50,348
She's bad at cleaning,
and her cooking's awful.

722
00:47:51,474 --> 00:47:53,267
Still, you love her, right?

723
00:48:01,317 --> 00:48:04,278
Of course.
I love her.

724
00:48:05,404 --> 00:48:07,240
We'll call it love.

725
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:10,993
Then would this help?

726
00:48:15,122 --> 00:48:17,500
The Care?
What is this?

727
00:48:17,708 --> 00:48:20,086
I just recently
found out about them.

728
00:48:20,294 --> 00:48:24,799
How to describe it?
It's like a membership service.

729
00:48:25,716 --> 00:48:32,098
The company provides veteran-grade
help to VIP customers such as you.

730
00:48:32,348 --> 00:48:38,187
For example maids, caregivers,
or drivers like myself.

731
00:48:38,354 --> 00:48:41,190
You can tell from the card
they're high-class.

732
00:48:41,941 --> 00:48:43,317
Cool design.

733
00:48:44,735 --> 00:48:46,821
Then how do you
know about this company?

734
00:48:46,862 --> 00:48:51,033
They contacted me,
as a veteran-grade driver.

735
00:48:51,450 --> 00:48:53,327
You might say they scouted me?

736
00:48:54,954 --> 00:49:00,918
But when their call came I had
already arranged to meet with you.

737
00:49:01,085 --> 00:49:03,921
I see...

738
00:49:05,256 --> 00:49:08,217
You turned down this
famous company to work for me.

739
00:49:08,968 --> 00:49:10,136
I won't forget that.

740
00:49:11,762 --> 00:49:13,931
Son of a bitch!

741
00:49:15,975 --> 00:49:20,062
Anyway, I can give this card
to my wife, right?

742
00:49:20,271 --> 00:49:22,023
Yes, that's why I brought it up.

743
00:49:22,106 --> 00:49:23,941
No need to mention me.

744
00:49:25,276 --> 00:49:28,571
You can tell her
you found the company yourself.

745
00:49:29,280 --> 00:49:30,448
Sure.

746
00:49:30,906 --> 00:49:33,159
Thanks to you I can
play the good husband.

747
00:49:33,367 --> 00:49:38,039
On the back, there's
a number for consultations.

748
00:49:38,205 --> 00:49:39,457
Tell her to call there...

749
00:49:39,498 --> 00:49:40,666
Eyes on the road!

750
00:49:45,921 --> 00:49:48,966
Hello, this is Senior Advisor Yeo
of The Care.

751
00:49:49,425 --> 00:49:52,595
Yes, this is The Care's main office?

752
00:49:52,720 --> 00:49:53,596
That's correct.

753
00:49:53,721 --> 00:49:57,099
If she wanted, she'd be
a fucking great con artist.

754
00:49:57,224 --> 00:49:59,477
Isn't her voice tone great?
Takes after me.

755
00:50:01,145 --> 00:50:03,689
From what I've heard,
it's a full membership service?

756
00:50:04,023 --> 00:50:07,902
So you're not currently
a member, I assume?

757
00:50:07,943 --> 00:50:10,488
<i>That's right.
What steps do I need to take?</i>

758
00:50:10,613 --> 00:50:14,700
We'll just need to receive
a few documents from you.

759
00:50:14,825 --> 00:50:17,495
Are you ready to write this down?

760
00:50:17,912 --> 00:50:22,416
Your family register,
citizenship ID cards...

761
00:50:23,459 --> 00:50:26,295
...documents to prove
your income level,

762
00:50:26,545 --> 00:50:28,923
i.e. the title to your property, etc.

763
00:50:29,048 --> 00:50:31,133
Our property title?
Yes.

764
00:50:39,850 --> 00:50:41,143
Wow, peaches!

765
00:50:41,477 --> 00:50:43,229
You have some too, Mr. Kevin.

766
00:50:43,688 --> 00:50:44,730
Thank you.

767
00:50:53,572 --> 00:50:56,534
Leave it outside the door
next time.

768
00:50:56,701 --> 00:50:58,452
- And knock!
- Yes.

769
00:51:01,372 --> 00:51:02,957
No entering during my lesson!

770
00:51:03,082 --> 00:51:04,166
Yes, miss!

771
00:51:06,585 --> 00:51:07,837
<i>Park Da-song!</i>

772
00:51:08,087 --> 00:51:09,171
Daddy!

773
00:51:09,463 --> 00:51:10,548
<i>Where are you?</i>

774
00:51:15,302 --> 00:51:16,262
Daddy!

775
00:51:16,595 --> 00:51:17,430
Son!

776
00:51:17,513 --> 00:51:19,265
Walkie talkies!

777
00:51:19,390 --> 00:51:20,182
Walkie talkies?

778
00:51:20,307 --> 00:51:21,267
Walkie talkies!

779
00:51:21,475 --> 00:51:24,353
Who do you like better,
your dad or the walkie talkie?

780
00:51:25,396 --> 00:51:27,982
Da-song, how could you
run out from your lesson?

781
00:51:28,733 --> 00:51:31,944
When did you buy all this?

782
00:51:32,027 --> 00:51:32,945
It's no big deal.

783
00:51:33,112 --> 00:51:33,779
Huh?

784
00:51:37,324 --> 00:51:37,992
Huh?

785
00:51:38,993 --> 00:51:40,077
What is it?

786
00:51:43,038 --> 00:51:44,165
What's he doing now?

787
00:51:45,708 --> 00:51:46,709
Da-song, don't do that!

788
00:51:46,834 --> 00:51:50,504
It's the same!
They smell the same!

789
00:51:50,755 --> 00:51:54,091
What are you talking about?
Go up to Jessica.

790
00:51:54,425 --> 00:51:58,179
Jessica smells like that, too.

791
00:51:59,263 --> 00:52:02,892
So do we all need to use
different soap, now?

792
00:52:02,933 --> 00:52:06,729
Dad, we'll need to use
different laundry soap, too.

793
00:52:06,937 --> 00:52:08,105
And fabric softener.

794
00:52:08,147 --> 00:52:12,109
You mean doing four separate
loads of laundry each time?

795
00:52:12,568 --> 00:52:14,111
That's not it.

796
00:52:15,070 --> 00:52:16,989
It's the semi-basement smell.

797
00:52:18,157 --> 00:52:20,826
We need to leave this home
to lose the smell.

798
00:52:22,787 --> 00:52:28,834
Anyway, aren't we fortunate to be
worrying about things like this?

799
00:52:28,876 --> 00:52:29,627
Sure.

800
00:52:30,044 --> 00:52:32,838
In an age like ours,

801
00:52:33,255 --> 00:52:37,718
when an opening for a security guard
attracts 500 university graduates.

802
00:52:38,052 --> 00:52:40,930
Our entire family got hired!

803
00:52:41,806 --> 00:52:43,140
That's right, Dad!

804
00:52:43,808 --> 00:52:46,227
If we put our 4 salaries together?

805
00:52:46,560 --> 00:52:50,564
The amount of cash coming from
that house into ours is immense!

806
00:52:51,482 --> 00:52:55,945
Let's offer a prayer of gratitude
to the great Mr. Park.

807
00:52:56,111 --> 00:52:57,154
And to Min!

808
00:52:57,321 --> 00:53:00,032
Ki-woo, that friend of yours
turned into such a fine guy,

809
00:53:00,074 --> 00:53:04,036
and thanks to him we're all...
Fuck, not again!

810
00:53:09,124 --> 00:53:09,959
That asshole's dead.

811
00:53:10,000 --> 00:53:12,586
Ki-woo's on the rampage!

812
00:53:12,628 --> 00:53:14,964
Don't overdo it!

813
00:53:16,131 --> 00:53:18,592
Use this instead.

814
00:53:22,346 --> 00:53:23,764
Damn you!

815
00:53:26,433 --> 00:53:27,893
Get a fucking grip!

816
00:53:27,935 --> 00:53:29,562
Get a grip!

817
00:53:31,856 --> 00:53:33,315
Wow!

818
00:53:37,528 --> 00:53:39,822
It's a deluge!

819
00:53:55,963 --> 00:54:00,426
Current weather is clear, over.
The clouds are moving.

820
00:54:00,467 --> 00:54:02,928
<i>But they're not rain clouds, over.</i>

821
00:54:02,970 --> 00:54:04,430
I hear you, over.

822
00:54:04,471 --> 00:54:10,644
Currently your sister's lip
is pouting like a duck's bill.

823
00:54:10,895 --> 00:54:13,522
She's super annoyed, over.

824
00:54:13,981 --> 00:54:18,527
Can't I stay home and study English?
And call Kevin?

825
00:54:18,777 --> 00:54:22,239
Hey! Don't make a scene
just as we're leaving.

826
00:54:22,281 --> 00:54:24,658
If we have to go,
let's have fun.

827
00:54:24,700 --> 00:54:27,369
Da-hye, this is no
ordinary camping trip.

828
00:54:27,411 --> 00:54:28,245
That's right!

829
00:54:28,287 --> 00:54:30,372
How could you miss
your brother's birthday?

830
00:54:30,414 --> 00:54:31,123
No way!

831
00:54:31,206 --> 00:54:33,542
Even your busy father
is taking time off to go.

832
00:54:33,584 --> 00:54:36,170
Right! If you don't go,
you'll regret it!

833
00:54:38,797 --> 00:54:40,883
Oh, right.
You know the beam projector?

834
00:54:41,091 --> 00:54:42,051
The outdoor theater?

835
00:54:42,092 --> 00:54:43,969
Right, bring the outdoor
beam projector.

836
00:54:44,011 --> 00:54:44,678
Yes.

837
00:54:44,803 --> 00:54:48,974
And look for Da-song's
camping raincoat.

838
00:54:49,391 --> 00:54:50,976
He loves it when it rains.

839
00:54:51,518 --> 00:54:55,397
You remember now?
Zoonie, Berry, and Foofoo.

840
00:54:55,439 --> 00:54:56,690
Zoonie and Berry get this.

841
00:54:56,815 --> 00:54:59,568
Yes, Natural Balance Original Ultra.

842
00:54:59,735 --> 00:55:01,862
Right, and for Foofoo...

843
00:55:02,404 --> 00:55:03,989
Kani-kamaboko.
Japanese crab sticks.

844
00:55:04,031 --> 00:55:04,990
Yes.

845
00:55:05,115 --> 00:55:07,993
When you walk Zoonie,
give him a long leash.

846
00:55:08,202 --> 00:55:10,579
He needs to run around
to feel happy.

847
00:55:10,621 --> 00:55:13,707
He's like the canine version
of Da-song!

848
00:55:39,650 --> 00:55:41,235
Son!

849
00:55:41,485 --> 00:55:44,405
Why are you lying down outside?

850
00:55:44,655 --> 00:55:47,199
Isn't he hot out there?

851
00:55:47,866 --> 00:55:52,454
I'm gazing at the sky from home.

852
00:55:54,289 --> 00:55:55,541
It's so great.

853
00:55:59,253 --> 00:56:01,422
Mom, want some water?

854
00:56:01,505 --> 00:56:02,756
There's sparkling, right?

855
00:56:03,090 --> 00:56:05,426
Ki-jung, some water?

856
00:56:05,676 --> 00:56:07,469
Telepathy... thank you.

857
00:56:29,908 --> 00:56:31,160
Whoa.

858
00:56:33,704 --> 00:56:36,373
Wow, all these
varieties of alcohol.

859
00:56:37,833 --> 00:56:41,253
Dad! Let me add
another to the mix!

860
00:56:41,295 --> 00:56:45,466
This is pretty classy.

861
00:56:46,300 --> 00:56:51,305
Rain falling on the lawn,
as we sip our whiskey...

862
00:56:51,555 --> 00:56:55,976
Ki-woo, what's that yellow
notebook you've been carrying?

863
00:56:56,935 --> 00:57:00,397
This? It's Da-hye's diary.

864
00:57:00,522 --> 00:57:01,982
Her diary?

865
00:57:02,066 --> 00:57:06,028
What a scumbag.
How could you read her diary?

866
00:57:06,862 --> 00:57:12,117
Just so we can
understand each other deeper.

867
00:57:12,242 --> 00:57:14,620
Fuck, are you two dating?

868
00:57:15,162 --> 00:57:19,291
I'm serious.
She really likes me too.

869
00:57:21,335 --> 00:57:22,628
A while back...

870
00:57:23,837 --> 00:57:24,922
Never mind.

871
00:57:25,964 --> 00:57:29,051
When she enters university,
I'll officially ask her out.

872
00:57:29,343 --> 00:57:30,344
Seriously.

873
00:57:35,265 --> 00:57:37,017
My son!

874
00:57:37,476 --> 00:57:41,730
Then this house will be
your in-laws' house?

875
00:57:44,399 --> 00:57:45,359
That's right.

876
00:57:45,609 --> 00:57:49,446
Fuck, then I'm washing dishes
at my daughter-in-law's?

877
00:57:49,488 --> 00:57:52,866
Sure, washing your
daughter-in-law's socks!

878
00:58:04,711 --> 00:58:09,883
I like her.
She's a good kid.

879
00:58:10,300 --> 00:58:14,263
She's pretty,
but she's not wild.

880
00:58:15,305 --> 00:58:19,476
Well, now that
we're daydreaming...

881
00:58:20,894 --> 00:58:23,564
If Da-hye and I marry,

882
00:58:23,605 --> 00:58:27,109
we can bring in actors
to be my mom and dad.

883
00:58:28,152 --> 00:58:28,986
Look at her.

884
00:58:29,528 --> 00:58:33,073
She got so many jobs
acting in weddings last year.

885
00:58:33,448 --> 00:58:37,703
I even caught the bouquet
from a bitch I've never met.

886
00:58:37,911 --> 00:58:40,789
If you get the bouquet,
they pay an extra $10.

887
00:58:40,956 --> 00:58:43,083
That's how your acting
got so good!

888
00:58:43,125 --> 00:58:48,505
Acting is one thing, but this
family is so gullible, right?

889
00:58:48,672 --> 00:58:50,924
The madame especially.

890
00:58:50,966 --> 00:58:52,634
You said it.

891
00:58:54,469 --> 00:58:57,806
She's so naive,
and nice.

892
00:58:58,182 --> 00:59:00,100
She's rich, but still nice.

893
00:59:00,184 --> 00:59:02,311
Not "rich, but still nice."

894
00:59:02,686 --> 00:59:06,231
"Nice because she's rich."
You know?

895
00:59:06,857 --> 00:59:13,322
Hell, if I had all this money.

896
00:59:14,489 --> 00:59:18,410
I'd be nice too!

897
00:59:18,702 --> 00:59:19,828
Even nicer!

898
00:59:20,370 --> 00:59:22,539
That's true.
Your mom's right.

899
00:59:22,789 --> 00:59:24,917
Rich people are naive.
No resentments.

900
00:59:25,292 --> 00:59:27,544
No creases on them.

901
00:59:27,669 --> 00:59:30,923
It all gets ironed out.
Money is an iron.

902
00:59:31,173 --> 00:59:33,634
Those creases all get smoothed out.

903
00:59:33,675 --> 00:59:34,843
Hey, Ki-woo.

904
00:59:35,802 --> 00:59:40,557
You know that driver, Yoon?
Was it Yoon?

905
00:59:41,099 --> 00:59:43,477
The driver before me.

906
00:59:43,727 --> 00:59:44,853
Yeah, Yoon.

907
00:59:45,020 --> 00:59:49,566
He must be working
somewhere else now, right?

908
00:59:49,733 --> 00:59:52,069
Sure, he must be.

909
00:59:52,110 --> 00:59:55,364
He's young,
got a nice physique.

910
00:59:55,906 --> 00:59:58,992
He must've found a better job.

911
00:59:59,034 --> 01:00:01,203
Fucking hell!

912
01:00:02,037 --> 01:00:04,289
What's with her now?

913
01:00:04,623 --> 01:00:10,796
We're the ones who need help.
Worry about us, okay?

914
01:00:11,255 --> 01:00:14,466
Dad! Come on, Dad!

915
01:00:14,758 --> 01:00:18,971
Just focus on us, okay?
On us!

916
01:00:19,137 --> 01:00:23,308
Not Driver Yoon, but me, please!

917
01:00:23,558 --> 01:00:25,811
Awesome timing, huh?

918
01:00:25,936 --> 01:00:29,690
She speaks,
and the lightning crashes!

919
01:00:31,650 --> 01:00:34,403
Hey, Jessica. Cheers.

920
01:00:35,445 --> 01:00:41,243
Hey, when I went up before,
and you were in the bath...

921
01:00:41,368 --> 01:00:42,911
What about it?

922
01:00:43,745 --> 01:00:46,999
How to put it?
You fit in here.

923
01:00:47,291 --> 01:00:50,127
This rich house suits you.
Not like us.

924
01:00:50,168 --> 01:00:51,044
Fuck off.

925
01:00:51,169 --> 01:00:52,045
I'm serious!

926
01:00:52,087 --> 01:00:53,839
Dad, before...

927
01:00:53,880 --> 01:00:56,425
She was lying back in the tub,
watching TV.

928
01:00:57,175 --> 01:00:59,511
Like she's lived here for years.

929
01:01:01,388 --> 01:01:07,269
Speaking of which,
if this became our house,

930
01:01:07,477 --> 01:01:11,565
if we lived here,
which room would you want?

931
01:01:11,815 --> 01:01:16,945
What room in this masterwork
by the great Namgoong?

932
01:01:17,112 --> 01:01:19,031
Fuck, I don't know.

933
01:01:19,072 --> 01:01:22,534
Get me the house first.
Then I'll think about it.

934
01:01:23,076 --> 01:01:25,162
We live here now, don't we?

935
01:01:25,829 --> 01:01:29,541
Getting drunk in the living room.

936
01:01:29,708 --> 01:01:32,753
Right, we live here.
Why not?

937
01:01:32,836 --> 01:01:37,299
This is our home right now.
It's cosy.

938
01:01:37,591 --> 01:01:40,385
Cosy?
Are you feeling cosy?

939
01:01:40,635 --> 01:01:45,390
Sure, but suppose Park
walked through that door now.

940
01:01:46,141 --> 01:01:47,601
What about your dad?

941
01:01:47,726 --> 01:01:50,979
He'd run and hide
like a cockroach.

942
01:01:51,605 --> 01:01:54,107
Kids, you know at our house,

943
01:01:54,149 --> 01:01:59,696
when you turn on the light,
and the cockroaches scatter?

944
01:01:59,946 --> 01:02:01,490
You know what I mean?

945
01:02:02,449 --> 01:02:05,410
I'm getting fucking tired of this.

946
01:02:06,161 --> 01:02:07,829
- A cockroach?
- Yeah.

947
01:02:11,750 --> 01:02:13,335
Huh? What's wrong?

948
01:02:13,460 --> 01:02:14,836
What's the matter?

949
01:02:14,878 --> 01:02:18,590
Dad, don't do that.
You only live once.

950
01:02:25,847 --> 01:02:27,599
What the hell?

951
01:02:27,766 --> 01:02:29,434
I fooled you! Didn't I?

952
01:02:29,476 --> 01:02:30,727
Jesus, Dad.

953
01:02:30,894 --> 01:02:34,940
I fooled you too, Ki-woo?
Did it look for real?

954
01:02:35,065 --> 01:02:38,443
If it was for real,
I'd fucking kill you.

955
01:02:38,860 --> 01:02:42,531
What is this?
Fucking puppy.

956
01:02:48,412 --> 01:02:50,455
Who is it at this hour?

957
01:02:50,789 --> 01:02:52,332
What is it?

958
01:02:58,797 --> 01:02:59,965
What's she doing here?

959
01:03:00,006 --> 01:03:02,759
The old housekeeper?

960
01:03:03,385 --> 01:03:05,178
What's she here for?

961
01:03:05,720 --> 01:03:09,558
She won't stop ringing it.

962
01:03:10,725 --> 01:03:13,478
Raising a racket.

963
01:03:14,938 --> 01:03:15,856
Who is it?

964
01:03:15,939 --> 01:03:20,402
Oh, hello! I'm...

965
01:03:20,819 --> 01:03:22,487
The madame's not in, right?

966
01:03:22,529 --> 01:03:23,405
What?

967
01:03:23,530 --> 01:03:27,784
I worked here
for a very long time.

968
01:03:28,535 --> 01:03:34,166
Above the monitor there,
you see a photo of 3 dogs, right?

969
01:03:34,332 --> 01:03:35,792
Zoonie, Berry, Foofoo.

970
01:03:35,834 --> 01:03:40,213
I get it,
but why are you here?

971
01:03:40,464 --> 01:03:44,801
You're my successor
as housekeeper, right?

972
01:03:49,973 --> 01:03:51,600
Anyway...

973
01:03:52,350 --> 01:03:55,520
I'm very sorry to
call on you so late.

974
01:03:55,854 --> 01:03:57,397
It's just that...

975
01:03:57,939 --> 01:04:04,696
I forgot something in the
basement under the kitchen.

976
01:04:05,489 --> 01:04:11,620
When I left,
they pushed me out so quickly...

977
01:04:14,998 --> 01:04:16,833
Would you let me in?

978
01:04:19,169 --> 01:04:20,962
What do we do?

979
01:04:21,588 --> 01:04:23,757
This isn't in the plan.

980
01:04:31,598 --> 01:04:33,058
Sorry for the trouble.

981
01:04:34,100 --> 01:04:34,976
This way.

982
01:04:35,018 --> 01:04:36,353
Yes, thank you.

983
01:04:38,522 --> 01:04:40,649
You can put your raincoat...

984
01:04:40,774 --> 01:04:42,984
It'll just be a second.

985
01:04:43,902 --> 01:04:47,489
Quite a meal there.
That'll be a job to clean up.

986
01:04:47,697 --> 01:04:50,742
But what did you leave below?

987
01:04:55,497 --> 01:04:57,874
Want to come down with me?

988
01:04:59,000 --> 01:05:02,254
Well, just go ahead.

989
01:05:55,599 --> 01:05:58,643
Help me push this!

990
01:05:59,102 --> 01:06:01,646
Pull it! From over there.

991
01:06:01,688 --> 01:06:02,939
What?

992
01:06:03,398 --> 01:06:04,149
Pull!

993
01:06:06,985 --> 01:06:08,528
Pull it hard!

994
01:06:12,407 --> 01:06:13,575
Are you okay?

995
01:06:15,118 --> 01:06:16,369
Did I scare you?

996
01:06:18,997 --> 01:06:20,457
Thank you!

997
01:06:21,916 --> 01:06:22,959
Thank you.

998
01:06:31,426 --> 01:06:32,385
Honey!

999
01:06:32,427 --> 01:06:33,178
What the hell?

1000
01:06:34,929 --> 01:06:35,972
Hey!

1001
01:06:36,014 --> 01:06:37,474
Honey!

1002
01:06:38,642 --> 01:06:40,060
Honey!

1003
01:06:42,646 --> 01:06:43,480
Wait!

1004
01:06:43,897 --> 01:06:45,982
Honey, I'm here!

1005
01:06:46,149 --> 01:06:47,108
What is all this?

1006
01:06:49,944 --> 01:06:50,487
Honey!

1007
01:06:51,404 --> 01:06:53,114
Honey, I'm fine.

1008
01:06:53,156 --> 01:06:54,616
No you're not!

1009
01:06:55,158 --> 01:06:56,076
I'm fine, really.

1010
01:06:56,117 --> 01:06:57,410
How can you say that?

1011
01:06:57,452 --> 01:06:59,287
But I'm really hungry.

1012
01:06:59,329 --> 01:07:00,288
Suck it!

1013
01:07:00,330 --> 01:07:03,291
How many days has it been?

1014
01:07:03,625 --> 01:07:05,001
You must've been so hungry!

1015
01:07:07,337 --> 01:07:08,588
It's okay.

1016
01:07:08,755 --> 01:07:11,424
She's a nice woman.
She let me in.

1017
01:07:11,549 --> 01:07:13,718
There was an iron plate,
for grilling meat.

1018
01:07:13,760 --> 01:07:15,303
It was wedged under the shelf.

1019
01:07:15,345 --> 01:07:16,429
So that's why.

1020
01:07:16,471 --> 01:07:19,808
I couldn't open it from the inside.

1021
01:07:19,974 --> 01:07:23,144
- What's going on here?
- I know you must be startled.

1022
01:07:23,645 --> 01:07:25,897
I would be too in this situation.

1023
01:07:26,356 --> 01:07:30,819
But as two fellow workers...
Right, Chung-sook?

1024
01:07:30,985 --> 01:07:33,446
How do you know my name?

1025
01:07:34,364 --> 01:07:38,827
To be honest I'm still texting
with the boy Da-song.

1026
01:07:39,160 --> 01:07:43,748
I knew they were going camping,
so I came today.

1027
01:07:43,790 --> 01:07:46,334
I wanted to speak to you alone.

1028
01:07:46,710 --> 01:07:47,544
<i>Talking about.</i>

1029
01:07:50,380 --> 01:07:52,674
Don't worry, Chung-sook.

1030
01:07:52,799 --> 01:07:56,344
I cut the wire
on the CCTV by the gate.

1031
01:07:56,678 --> 01:08:00,265
Nobody knows I came.
Isn't that good, sis?

1032
01:08:00,390 --> 01:08:02,475
Don't call me sis!

1033
01:08:02,517 --> 01:08:05,186
Sis, my name is Moon-gwang.

1034
01:08:05,729 --> 01:08:10,066
This is my hubbie Oh Geun-sae.
Say hello, honey.

1035
01:08:10,233 --> 01:08:13,570
This tastes great.
What happened to your face?

1036
01:08:13,611 --> 01:08:16,990
I'll tell you later.

1037
01:08:17,031 --> 01:08:20,994
So you'd steal food every day
while working in the kitchen.

1038
01:08:21,035 --> 01:08:22,162
Feeding your husband.

1039
01:08:22,203 --> 01:08:26,791
Not at all! I bought
all his food with my salary.

1040
01:08:26,916 --> 01:08:29,878
That's so unfair!

1041
01:08:30,128 --> 01:08:32,797
But how long has
your husband been down here?

1042
01:08:32,839 --> 01:08:35,300
Hold on a sec.
4 years?

1043
01:08:36,050 --> 01:08:38,887
4 years, 3 months
and 17 days.

1044
01:08:38,928 --> 01:08:40,597
Right, it's June now.

1045
01:08:41,264 --> 01:08:47,020
Four years ago when
Mr. Namgoong moved to Paris,

1046
01:08:47,520 --> 01:08:50,190
in the time before
Mr. Park's family moved in,

1047
01:08:50,648 --> 01:08:54,110
I brought my husband down here.

1048
01:08:54,235 --> 01:08:59,032
Many rich houses have secret bunkers,
where you can hide

1049
01:08:59,365 --> 01:09:03,620
in case North Korea attacks,
or if creditors break in.

1050
01:09:03,953 --> 01:09:09,834
But it seems Mr. Namgoong was
a bit embarrassed about this,

1051
01:09:10,293 --> 01:09:14,047
because he never mentioned it
to Mr. Park's family.

1052
01:09:14,297 --> 01:09:15,632
So only I know about it.

1053
01:09:15,673 --> 01:09:18,051
So that's how it happened.

1054
01:09:18,301 --> 01:09:22,430
But now that I know, I've no
choice but to call the police!

1055
01:09:22,472 --> 01:09:24,557
No please, sis!

1056
01:09:25,558 --> 01:09:27,852
As fellow members
of the needy, please don't.

1057
01:09:27,894 --> 01:09:29,354
I'm not needy!

1058
01:09:29,395 --> 01:09:33,066
But we're needy!

1059
01:09:33,316 --> 01:09:37,529
We've no house, no money,
only debts!

1060
01:09:37,904 --> 01:09:38,947
Sis, please!

1061
01:09:39,113 --> 01:09:43,535
Even after 4 years of hiding,
those debt collectors won't give up.

1062
01:09:43,701 --> 01:09:47,789
They're still searching for him,
threatening to stab him.

1063
01:09:47,914 --> 01:09:49,374
You used loan sharks?

1064
01:09:50,416 --> 01:09:52,293
It's all my fault.

1065
01:09:52,836 --> 01:09:54,087
The Taiwan cake shop.

1066
01:09:54,712 --> 01:09:58,800
My Taiwanese Wangshui
castella shop went bust.

1067
01:09:58,842 --> 01:10:01,052
I was overwhelmed by debt.

1068
01:10:01,219 --> 01:10:02,679
Please take this.

1069
01:10:03,137 --> 01:10:04,180
What's that?

1070
01:10:04,722 --> 01:10:08,810
It's not much,
just a modest sum.

1071
01:10:09,018 --> 01:10:11,688
But we'll send it
to you every month.

1072
01:10:12,105 --> 01:10:13,898
In return,
just once every 2 days,

1073
01:10:13,940 --> 01:10:17,068
please leave him some food.

1074
01:10:17,735 --> 01:10:20,613
No no, just once a week.

1075
01:10:21,322 --> 01:10:23,700
There's a refrigerator here.
Just once a week.

1076
01:10:23,741 --> 01:10:26,286
You've got some nerve!
I'm calling the police.

1077
01:10:26,327 --> 01:10:27,203
Sis!

1078
01:10:30,248 --> 01:10:31,416
Who is that?

1079
01:10:34,627 --> 01:10:36,337
Wait... Jessica?

1080
01:10:37,255 --> 01:10:38,131
Mr. Kim?

1081
01:10:38,381 --> 01:10:39,132
What the hell?

1082
01:10:40,758 --> 01:10:42,093
Dad, my ankle!

1083
01:10:42,135 --> 01:10:43,344
You okay? Sorry.

1084
01:10:43,386 --> 01:10:45,346
Dad, my foot.

1085
01:10:45,388 --> 01:10:46,723
Don't call me Dad!

1086
01:10:54,272 --> 01:10:58,109
I thought it was weird
when the driver was fired.

1087
01:10:59,193 --> 01:10:59,736
Hey!

1088
01:10:59,777 --> 01:11:02,238
- Let's talk things over.
- What the hell?

1089
01:11:02,280 --> 01:11:03,740
Are you some
family of charlatans?

1090
01:11:03,781 --> 01:11:04,657
So, sis...

1091
01:11:04,699 --> 01:11:06,868
Don't fucking call me sis,
you filthy bitch!

1092
01:11:07,410 --> 01:11:12,540
I'm gonna send this video
to the madame, how about that?

1093
01:11:12,582 --> 01:11:14,459
<i>Dad, my foot.</i>

1094
01:11:14,918 --> 01:11:16,753
No reception in
the basement, right?

1095
01:11:17,587 --> 01:11:19,547
- The phone works fine.
- Fuck.

1096
01:11:19,589 --> 01:11:24,260
Ma'am, to be honest,
the jobs we have here...

1097
01:11:24,302 --> 01:11:27,263
Shut up!
It's too late now!

1098
01:11:27,430 --> 01:11:30,767
Let's all go to jail!
We're fucking going down!

1099
01:11:30,808 --> 01:11:33,978
Lady, are you crazy?

1100
01:11:34,520 --> 01:11:39,567
If they see that video, Mr. Park
and his wife will be so shocked!

1101
01:11:39,943 --> 01:11:42,987
What did those nice people
ever do wrong?

1102
01:11:43,821 --> 01:11:44,697
Why do this to them?

1103
01:11:44,739 --> 01:11:46,157
Stop right there!

1104
01:11:46,532 --> 01:11:48,701
Or I'll push the 'send' button.

1105
01:11:49,035 --> 01:11:50,662
Follow me.

1106
01:11:51,245 --> 01:11:53,581
Calm down, ma'am.

1107
01:11:57,210 --> 01:11:59,212
Don't push!

1108
01:12:00,546 --> 01:12:01,714
Let's go up, honey.

1109
01:12:02,465 --> 01:12:05,176
Time for you
to get some fresh air!

1110
01:12:22,485 --> 01:12:28,533
Honey, this 'send' button
is like a missile launcher.

1111
01:12:28,992 --> 01:12:30,451
What do you mean, honey?

1112
01:12:31,369 --> 01:12:36,457
If we threaten to push it,
those people can't do anything.

1113
01:12:36,749 --> 01:12:40,920
It's like a North Korean rocket.
A North Korean missile button!

1114
01:12:42,505 --> 01:12:46,259
Today our beloved
Great Leader Kim Jong-un,

1115
01:12:46,300 --> 01:12:49,345
after witnessing the
charlatan family video,

1116
01:12:49,512 --> 01:12:52,265
was unable to contain
his shock and fury

1117
01:12:52,306 --> 01:12:55,643
at their wicked,
despicable provocation!

1118
01:12:55,685 --> 01:12:57,478
I've missed your jokes, honey!

1119
01:12:57,520 --> 01:13:02,150
Therefore our Great Leader,
in this age of denuclearization,

1120
01:13:02,191 --> 01:13:07,989
has commanded that the nation's
last remaining nuclear warhead

1121
01:13:08,031 --> 01:13:10,575
be driven down the throats
of this wicked family!

1122
01:13:10,616 --> 01:13:15,371
No one can imitate North Korean
news anchors like you!

1123
01:13:15,413 --> 01:13:20,501
With their stinking guts serving
as the last nuclear graveyard,

1124
01:13:20,543 --> 01:13:25,381
our Dear Leader's wish to denuclearize
and bring world peace can...

1125
01:13:25,548 --> 01:13:27,258
Hands in the air, fuckers!

1126
01:13:27,842 --> 01:13:28,885
Higher!

1127
01:13:31,137 --> 01:13:33,014
You scumbag family.

1128
01:13:33,306 --> 01:13:34,098
Husband?

1129
01:13:34,640 --> 01:13:35,308
Husband.

1130
01:13:35,349 --> 01:13:36,017
Wife?

1131
01:13:36,350 --> 01:13:36,976
Yes.

1132
01:13:37,226 --> 01:13:37,810
Son?

1133
01:13:38,352 --> 01:13:38,811
Yes.

1134
01:13:38,936 --> 01:13:39,520
Daughter?

1135
01:13:39,645 --> 01:13:40,188
Daughter.

1136
01:13:40,354 --> 01:13:42,190
You neanderthals.

1137
01:13:42,356 --> 01:13:46,486
Is that all you can think to do,
drink yourselves stupid?

1138
01:13:46,861 --> 01:13:51,908
In this home suffused with
Mr. Namgoong's creative spirit?

1139
01:13:52,241 --> 01:13:53,201
You cretins!

1140
01:13:53,367 --> 01:13:54,619
What do you know about art?

1141
01:13:54,744 --> 01:13:56,704
What would they know?

1142
01:13:57,663 --> 01:14:05,546
When the sun was nice,
we'd bask in those sunbeams, right?

1143
01:14:06,339 --> 01:14:10,718
At such moments we could feel
his artistic touch.

1144
01:14:58,808 --> 01:15:02,103
Give it to me!

1145
01:15:21,247 --> 01:15:24,709
Good job! Delete it!

1146
01:15:26,043 --> 01:15:28,296
Careful, don't send it
by accident.

1147
01:15:43,060 --> 01:15:43,936
Hello?

1148
01:15:44,854 --> 01:15:48,024
Listen, do you know how
to make ram-don?

1149
01:15:48,858 --> 01:15:50,026
Ram-don?

1150
01:15:50,193 --> 01:15:53,529
Da-song likes ram-don
more than anything.

1151
01:15:54,071 --> 01:15:57,450
If you boil the water now,
the timing will be perfect.

1152
01:15:57,867 --> 01:16:00,536
<i>There's sirloin in the fridge,
add that too.</i>

1153
01:16:00,703 --> 01:16:02,246
Then, the camping...?

1154
01:16:02,288 --> 01:16:05,666
<i>My god, what a disaster.</i>

1155
01:16:06,375 --> 01:16:11,464
The river overflowed and
everyone was packing their tents,

1156
01:16:11,964 --> 01:16:14,926
but Da-song was crying and
refusing to go home.

1157
01:16:15,092 --> 01:16:18,846
<i>Anyway, ram-don
as soon as we walk in, okay?</i>

1158
01:16:19,305 --> 01:16:21,557
Then you're almost here?

1159
01:16:21,891 --> 01:16:24,143
8 minutes,
according to the GPS.

1160
01:16:24,810 --> 01:16:25,937
You arrive in 8 minutes...

1161
01:16:25,978 --> 01:16:29,357
<i>Start boiling
the water right away!</i>

1162
01:16:33,736 --> 01:16:35,071
What the hell is ram-don?

1163
01:16:44,497 --> 01:16:45,957
Move, quickly!

1164
01:16:47,208 --> 01:16:48,668
Hurry!

1165
01:16:55,925 --> 01:16:57,677
<i>Ramen / Udon</i>

1166
01:16:59,428 --> 01:17:02,223
Dad, I can't drag her
any further!

1167
01:17:13,526 --> 01:17:15,194
What are you doing?

1168
01:17:16,654 --> 01:17:18,114
Dad!

1169
01:17:21,242 --> 01:17:24,412
Go up quickly!
Help upstairs.

1170
01:17:32,169 --> 01:17:32,837
Take this!

1171
01:17:52,690 --> 01:17:53,858
Welcome home!

1172
01:17:53,983 --> 01:17:57,028
Da-song, look!
Let's eat ram-don!

1173
01:17:59,488 --> 01:18:00,656
<i>Da-song!</i>

1174
01:18:03,617 --> 01:18:05,286
<i>Da-song!</i>

1175
01:18:11,917 --> 01:18:13,252
Madame!

1176
01:18:31,729 --> 01:18:33,981
Why don't you just
eat the ram-don?

1177
01:18:34,148 --> 01:18:34,774
Shall I?

1178
01:18:35,024 --> 01:18:37,985
No wait.
I can give it to my husband.

1179
01:18:38,152 --> 01:18:39,904
There's sirloin in here.

1180
01:18:42,656 --> 01:18:46,202
It's cooked through?
<i>Medium well done.</i>

1181
01:19:11,352 --> 01:19:17,441
<i>Returning after a day's work...
I love you so much, Mr. Park!</i>

1182
01:19:17,650 --> 01:19:23,823
<i>Home from the office,
Mr. Park is off duty now.</i>

1183
01:19:25,783 --> 01:19:30,162
Returning after a day's work...
I love you so much, Mr. Park!

1184
01:19:30,204 --> 01:19:31,956
- What are you doing?
- Shut up!

1185
01:19:43,717 --> 01:19:45,886
Honey, do you want
some ram-don?

1186
01:19:46,303 --> 01:19:47,388
Da-song doesn't want it?

1187
01:19:47,430 --> 01:19:48,055
No.

1188
01:19:48,222 --> 01:19:49,765
No, I'm tired.
I'm going to bed.

1189
01:19:50,433 --> 01:19:53,060
Why are you staring?

1190
01:19:54,395 --> 01:19:57,982
Mr. Park, you feed me
and house me.

1191
01:19:58,023 --> 01:19:59,191
<i>Respect!</i>

1192
01:20:01,444 --> 01:20:02,903
You do this every day?

1193
01:20:03,696 --> 01:20:08,909
Sure, I even send whole
sentences to thank him.

1194
01:20:09,702 --> 01:20:11,871
Someone of your age
should know it.

1195
01:20:12,037 --> 01:20:12,788
Know what?

1196
01:20:12,955 --> 01:20:14,415
Morse Code.

1197
01:20:15,332 --> 01:20:19,003
That sensor's going batty.

1198
01:20:27,553 --> 01:20:30,806
Da-song will know it,
since he's a Scout.

1199
01:20:31,140 --> 01:20:32,600
It's ridiculous, right?

1200
01:20:32,975 --> 01:20:36,103
Running around,
trying to please a kid.

1201
01:20:36,562 --> 01:20:38,314
He's not some kind of prince.

1202
01:20:38,647 --> 01:20:41,025
He's the youngest.
It's common.

1203
01:20:42,359 --> 01:20:43,611
Please understand.

1204
01:20:44,361 --> 01:20:47,907
Da-song is a bit... unwell.

1205
01:20:48,491 --> 01:20:51,202
He's receiving trauma therapy
and art therapy.

1206
01:20:52,453 --> 01:20:54,413
There was an incident.

1207
01:20:54,580 --> 01:20:55,623
What incident?

1208
01:20:56,248 --> 01:20:59,835
Sis, you believe in ghosts, too?

1209
01:21:01,295 --> 01:21:04,840
Da-song saw a ghost in the house
when he was in 1st grade.

1210
01:21:11,472 --> 01:21:13,849
He had a birthday party
at home that day.

1211
01:21:14,266 --> 01:21:16,727
Late that night,
when everyone was sleeping,

1212
01:21:16,810 --> 01:21:21,065
Da-song crept down to the kitchen
and took the cake out.

1213
01:21:21,482 --> 01:21:24,485
The whipped cream
on that cake was amazing.

1214
01:21:24,610 --> 01:21:27,238
Even in bed, he couldn't
stop thinking about it.

1215
01:21:27,821 --> 01:21:33,160
So Da-song was sitting,
eating his cake...

1216
01:21:43,003 --> 01:21:45,673
He screamed,
and I ran downstairs,

1217
01:21:46,423 --> 01:21:48,175
and he was all...

1218
01:21:49,051 --> 01:21:54,014
his eyes rolled back in his head,
convulsions, foam in his mouth.

1219
01:21:56,308 --> 01:21:58,602
Have you ever seen a child
have a seizure?

1220
01:21:58,727 --> 01:21:59,520
No.

1221
01:21:59,562 --> 01:22:04,692
They need 15-minute treatment,
or they're done for.

1222
01:22:04,942 --> 01:22:09,822
That's the time you have to reach
an emergency room, 15 minutes.

1223
01:22:11,657 --> 01:22:15,911
How can you live
in a place like this?

1224
01:22:16,036 --> 01:22:19,039
Well, lots of people
live underground.

1225
01:22:19,331 --> 01:22:21,208
Especially if you count
semi-basements.

1226
01:22:21,333 --> 01:22:25,546
What'll you do?
You don't have a plan?

1227
01:22:26,088 --> 01:22:29,341
I just feel comfortable here.

1228
01:22:30,759 --> 01:22:33,637
It feels like I was born here.

1229
01:22:34,680 --> 01:22:37,641
Maybe I had
my wedding here, too.

1230
01:22:38,058 --> 01:22:41,145
As for the National Pension,
I don't qualify.

1231
01:22:42,605 --> 01:22:45,858
In my old age,
love will comfort me.

1232
01:22:47,610 --> 01:22:52,823
So please.
Let me live down here.

1233
01:22:54,617 --> 01:22:56,076
Anyway...

1234
01:22:56,785 --> 01:23:01,665
My husband was away on business,
so I had to deal with it all.

1235
01:23:02,625 --> 01:23:06,754
Since then we've always
gone out for his birthday.

1236
01:23:07,004 --> 01:23:09,757
Last year my mother's house,
this year, camping.

1237
01:23:10,132 --> 01:23:14,762
Da-song's dad says it's
just a part of growing up.

1238
01:23:15,137 --> 01:23:19,600
They say a ghost in the
house brings wealth.

1239
01:23:21,143 --> 01:23:25,773
Actually, the money's
been good recently.

1240
01:23:52,675 --> 01:23:54,426
Thank god.

1241
01:24:20,994 --> 01:24:23,914
Just stay here for now.

1242
01:24:34,800 --> 01:24:36,552
Zoonie, what's wrong?

1243
01:24:38,804 --> 01:24:40,055
Something under there?

1244
01:24:42,015 --> 01:24:43,434
What is it?

1245
01:24:44,727 --> 01:24:45,686
Damn it!

1246
01:24:47,479 --> 01:24:48,480
- Mom!
- Yeah?

1247
01:24:48,689 --> 01:24:50,983
- How could you?
- What?

1248
01:24:51,191 --> 01:24:55,070
I like ram-don too!
How could you not even ask me?

1249
01:24:55,529 --> 01:24:56,196
Well...

1250
01:24:56,238 --> 01:25:00,284
Da-song didn't want it, so you
asked Dad, then ate it yourself.

1251
01:25:00,409 --> 01:25:01,285
Want her to make one?

1252
01:25:01,326 --> 01:25:03,287
That's not the point!

1253
01:25:03,328 --> 01:25:07,082
- Stop fighting over ramen!
- Why didn't you ask me?

1254
01:25:07,124 --> 01:25:10,294
Oh, stop it! Just go to bed.
Go get changed.

1255
01:25:14,214 --> 01:25:15,466
This way!

1256
01:25:17,760 --> 01:25:18,218
And Ki-jung?

1257
01:25:18,260 --> 01:25:21,221
Under there! Hurry!

1258
01:25:24,725 --> 01:25:27,102
One, two, three! One, two three!

1259
01:25:27,144 --> 01:25:28,395
Da-song?

1260
01:25:28,645 --> 01:25:31,023
Da-song, cut it out!

1261
01:25:31,648 --> 01:25:34,026
He's gone crazy!
Get an umbrella.

1262
01:25:34,568 --> 01:25:35,736
Hey Park Da-song!

1263
01:25:37,571 --> 01:25:42,409
What a monster.
What the hell is he doing?

1264
01:25:42,451 --> 01:25:46,330
Da-song, it's time for bed!
You know how late it is?

1265
01:25:46,371 --> 01:25:47,039
Here.

1266
01:25:48,290 --> 01:25:49,333
Honey, here.

1267
01:25:53,295 --> 01:25:59,635
Who do you take after to be
so stubborn! Look at this rain!

1268
01:26:05,307 --> 01:26:08,018
<i>OMG Kevin.
Da-song camping in the yard.</i>

1269
01:26:11,897 --> 01:26:16,026
Hey, channel 3 for emergencies!
Keep it turned on.

1270
01:26:16,902 --> 01:26:20,072
Let me have it.
I can't believe him.

1271
01:26:20,197 --> 01:26:22,533
Just leave him.
He'll come in if he's tired.

1272
01:26:23,075 --> 01:26:25,786
<i>- I want you here, honey.
- I'm with you.</i>

1273
01:26:25,911 --> 01:26:27,037
Hey, Da-hye!

1274
01:26:27,204 --> 01:26:29,456
Stop using your phone.
Go to bed.

1275
01:26:30,123 --> 01:26:32,668
Go sleep in your room.
We'll take care of things.

1276
01:26:32,918 --> 01:26:35,963
This is the living room,
do you copy?

1277
01:26:36,004 --> 01:26:37,172
<i>Copy, over.</i>

1278
01:26:37,214 --> 01:26:41,385
Daddy is standing by
for emergencies, over.

1279
01:26:41,510 --> 01:26:43,971
<i>Got it, over.</i>

