1535
01:50:36,777 --> 01:50:39,989
Hey, are you okay?

1536
01:50:45,369 --> 01:50:46,537
Are you...?

1537
01:50:56,588 --> 01:50:57,840
Wait, mister!

1538
01:52:45,197 --> 01:52:47,866
Kevin? Kevin!

1539
01:52:54,706 --> 01:52:57,459
Da-song, <i>happy birthday!</i>

1540
01:52:57,584 --> 01:52:58,752
Congratulations!

1541
01:53:06,427 --> 01:53:07,469
Shit...

1542
01:53:17,521 --> 01:53:19,481
<i>Stop!</i>

1543
01:53:19,606 --> 01:53:21,775
Chung-sook!

1544
01:53:21,817 --> 01:53:22,651
Ki-jung!

1545
01:53:22,734 --> 01:53:24,194
Come out here, Chung-sook!

1546
01:53:24,236 --> 01:53:27,698
Stop the blood!
Push down on the wound!

1547
01:53:32,536 --> 01:53:33,370
Da-song!

1548
01:53:34,413 --> 01:53:35,205
Honey!

1549
01:53:37,040 --> 01:53:38,792
Let go, don't!

1550
01:53:49,761 --> 01:53:51,180
It hurts.

1551
01:53:56,351 --> 01:53:57,311
The emergency room!

1552
01:53:57,436 --> 01:53:58,729
Get the car!

1553
01:53:58,770 --> 01:54:00,731
Mr. Kim!
What are you doing?

1554
01:54:00,939 --> 01:54:02,441
We can't wait for an ambulance!

1555
01:54:02,941 --> 01:54:05,110
Stop pushing, Dad!

1556
01:54:05,360 --> 01:54:08,030
Makes it hurt more.

1557
01:54:09,072 --> 01:54:10,032
Car keys!
The car keys!

1558
01:54:10,157 --> 01:54:12,951
Throw them!
Throw me the keys!

1559
01:54:30,761 --> 01:54:32,054
Are you okay?

1560
01:54:32,596 --> 01:54:34,056
Don't touch it!

1561
01:54:36,517 --> 01:54:38,644
Hello, Mr. Park.

1562
01:54:39,102 --> 01:54:39,978
You know me?

1563
01:54:40,312 --> 01:54:41,647
<i>Respect!</i>

1564
01:56:08,609 --> 01:56:12,070
<i>Opening my eyes for
the first time in a month,</i>

1565
01:56:12,112 --> 01:56:13,572
<i>I saw a detective.</i>

1566
01:56:14,072 --> 01:56:18,869
You have the right
to an attorney...

1567
01:56:18,910 --> 01:56:20,871
<i>Who looked nothing
like a detective.</i>

1568
01:56:25,500 --> 01:56:27,169
Is he laughing?

1569
01:56:27,586 --> 01:56:28,879
Just a sec.

1570
01:56:29,630 --> 01:56:34,176
<i>Then the doctor who looked
nothing like a doctor spoke.</i>

1571
01:56:35,510 --> 01:56:39,097
That happens sometimes
after brain surgery.

1572
01:56:39,431 --> 01:56:41,391
They keep laughing.
For no reason.

1573
01:56:42,309 --> 01:56:44,186
Do you hear me?

1574
01:56:44,728 --> 01:56:46,271
Can you hear me?

1575
01:56:46,730 --> 01:56:48,482
Then do I have to do it again?

1576
01:56:48,649 --> 01:56:49,399
Do what?

1577
01:56:49,524 --> 01:56:50,776
The Miranda thing.

1578
01:56:53,320 --> 01:56:57,491
You have the right to remain silent.

1579
01:56:57,532 --> 01:57:00,202
Anything you say can and
will be used against you...

1580
01:57:00,410 --> 01:57:02,412
He keeps laughing, look!

1581
01:57:05,749 --> 01:57:11,588
<i>Even when I heard how much
Ki-jung bled that day...</i>

1582
01:57:14,049 --> 01:57:21,223
<i>Even when I heard the words forgery,
trespassing, foul play, self-defense</i>

1583
01:57:21,556 --> 01:57:25,602
<i>and we were lucky to
get away with a probation...</i>

1584
01:57:28,939 --> 01:57:32,025
<i>Even when I finally
got to see Ki-jung's face...</i>

1585
01:57:32,067 --> 01:57:34,736
<i>Kim Ki-jung, RIP</i>

1586
01:57:36,488 --> 01:57:38,615
<i>I kept laughing.</i>

1587
01:57:48,583 --> 01:57:53,839
<i>Still, when I went back and
watched the news reports,</i>

1588
01:57:54,214 --> 01:57:55,340
<i>I didn't laugh.</i>

1589
01:57:55,507 --> 01:57:59,553
This sudden rampage in the
back yard of an upper-class home

1590
01:57:59,678 --> 01:58:01,263
is a highly unusual case.

1591
01:58:01,388 --> 01:58:05,767
Since the homeless man who sparked
the rampage died at the scene,

1592
01:58:05,892 --> 01:58:11,273
police are struggling to even
establish a clear motive.

1593
01:58:11,314 --> 01:58:15,777
The driver Kim and the slain Mr. Park
are said to have been on good terms.

1594
01:58:15,902 --> 01:58:21,074
For now the police investigation is
focused on locating the driver Kim.

1595
01:58:21,825 --> 01:58:25,454
Kim, after exiting this door
and descending the stairs,

1596
01:58:25,829 --> 01:58:28,999
disappeared into the
neighboring alleys.

1597
01:58:29,833 --> 01:58:34,671
Police searched the CCTVs
of nearby homes to no avail,

1598
01:58:35,338 --> 01:58:38,300
and they have yet
to find any witnesses.

1599
01:58:39,050 --> 01:58:41,011
Given the situation,

1600
01:58:41,344 --> 01:58:46,308
it's not an exaggeration to say
that Kim vanished into thin air.

1601
01:58:47,768 --> 01:58:54,691
<i>Actually Mom and I had
no idea where Dad was.</i>

1602
01:58:56,943 --> 01:59:02,407
<i>But those detectives still
wore themselves out tailing us.</i>

1603
01:59:06,536 --> 01:59:12,417
<i>Eventually the news went quiet,
and after the tails stopped,</i>

1604
01:59:13,084 --> 01:59:16,338
<i>I started going up that mountain.</i>

1605
01:59:18,590 --> 01:59:23,136
<i>From up there, you get
a great view of the house.</i>

1606
01:59:26,181 --> 01:59:33,271
<i>That day, despite the cold,
I felt like staying longer.</i>

1607
01:59:46,409 --> 01:59:49,871
Dash-dash-dot-dot

1608
02:00:15,230 --> 02:00:16,314
Son!

1609
02:00:18,525 --> 02:00:19,693
<i>Son!</i>

1610
02:00:22,028 --> 02:00:25,574
<i>Perhaps you, if no one else,
will be able to read this letter.</i>

1611
02:00:29,160 --> 02:00:35,417
<i>You were a Boy Scout,
so I'm writing this just in case.</i>

1612
02:00:38,753 --> 02:00:41,423
<i>Have your injuries healed?</i>

1613
02:00:42,674 --> 02:00:46,720
<i>I'm sure your mom
is plenty healthy.</i>

1614
02:00:50,849 --> 02:00:53,602
<i>I'm doing fine in here.</i>

1615
02:00:54,686 --> 02:00:57,355
<i>Though thinking
of Ki-jung makes me cry.</i>

1616
02:01:00,775 --> 02:01:05,238
<i>Even now, what happened
that day doesn't seem real.</i>

1617
02:01:06,573 --> 02:01:08,241
<i>It feels like a dream,</i>

1618
02:01:09,910 --> 02:01:11,745
<i>and yet it doesn't.</i>

1619
02:01:13,079 --> 02:01:17,751
<i>That day as I went out the gate,
I suddenly knew.</i>

1620
02:01:18,793 --> 02:01:20,545
<i>Where I needed to go...</i>

1621
02:02:00,251 --> 02:02:03,296
<i>A house where such
a grisly crime took place</i>

1622
02:02:03,338 --> 02:02:06,299
<i>would surely not
be easy to sell.</i>

1623
02:02:09,761 --> 02:02:12,013
I'm sorry, Mr. Park.

1624
02:02:12,263 --> 02:02:18,436
<i>I struggled to hold out
like that in an empty house.</i>

1625
02:02:21,272 --> 02:02:24,317
<i>Still, thanks to
the house being empty,</i>

1626
02:02:24,359 --> 02:02:29,239
<i>what was her name?
Moon-gwang?</i>

1627
02:02:29,280 --> 02:02:33,243
<i>I was able to give her
a proper send off.</i>

1628
02:02:34,744 --> 02:02:41,126
<i>I hear tree-side burials are trendy,
so hell, I did my best.</i>

1629
02:02:44,796 --> 02:02:48,341
<i>But those real estate sharks
sure are clever.</i>

1630
02:02:52,971 --> 02:02:57,475
<i>They hoodwinked some people
who had just arrived in Korea</i>

1631
02:02:57,517 --> 02:02:59,561
<i>and managed to sell the house.</i>

1632
02:03:01,021 --> 02:03:04,357
<i>With the parents working,
and the kids attending school,</i>

1633
02:03:04,399 --> 02:03:06,651
<i>the family is usually out.</i>

1634
02:03:07,110 --> 02:03:12,157
<i>But the goddamned housekeeper
stays there 24 hours a day.</i>

1635
02:03:12,699 --> 02:03:17,287
<i>Each time I go upstairs,
I take my life in my hands.</i>

1636
02:03:20,123 --> 02:03:24,169
<i>It turns out Germans eat more
than just sausage and beer.</i>

1637
02:03:24,836 --> 02:03:26,755
<i>What a relief.</i>

1638
02:03:29,632 --> 02:03:33,678
<i>Passing the time down here,
everything starts to go hazy.</i>

1639
02:03:38,308 --> 02:03:42,395
<i>Today at least
I was able to write you a letter.</i>

1640
02:03:44,314 --> 02:03:48,276
<i>If I send out the letter
this way every night,</i>

1641
02:03:48,318 --> 02:03:52,405
<i>maybe someday you'll see it.</i>

1642
02:03:58,536 --> 02:04:00,538
<i>So long.</i>

1643
02:04:14,385 --> 02:04:15,553
You're home, Ki-woo?

1644
02:04:15,595 --> 02:04:16,221
Yeah.

1645
02:04:30,985 --> 02:04:35,740
<i>Dad, today I made a plan.</i>

1646
02:04:37,283 --> 02:04:39,244
<i>A fundamental plan.</i>

1647
02:04:42,288 --> 02:04:43,957
<i>I'm going to earn money.</i>

1648
02:04:44,874 --> 02:04:46,334
<i>A lot of it.</i>

1649
02:04:49,921 --> 02:04:54,384
<i>University, a career, marriage,
those are all fine,</i>

1650
02:04:54,884 --> 02:04:56,845
<i>but first I'll earn money.</i>

1651
02:04:57,011 --> 02:05:01,975
You'll see once you go in,
but it's very spacious.

1652
02:05:02,809 --> 02:05:07,480
Actually, we don't show
this house to just anyone.

1653
02:05:07,730 --> 02:05:11,901
<i>When I have money,
I'll buy that house.</i>

1654
02:05:13,027 --> 02:05:17,198
<i>On the day we move in,
Mom and I will be in the yard.</i>

1655
02:05:17,824 --> 02:05:20,118
<i>Because the sunshine
is so nice there.</i>

1656
02:05:21,661 --> 02:05:23,371
<i>All you'll need to do</i>

1657
02:05:23,830 --> 02:05:26,416
<i>is walk up the stairs.</i>

1658
02:06:49,332 --> 02:06:53,169
<i>Take care until then.</i>

1659
02:06:58,132 --> 02:06:59,968
<i>So long.</i>

